Synopsis:
Yash Raj Films’ Saiyaara is an intense love story, that launches Ahaan Panday and Aneet Padda as the next YRF hero and heroine respectively. 

Directed by Mohit Suri, a master of the romance genre, Saiyaara tells a pure-hearted love story of two youngsters Vaani and Krish. While Vaani writes, Krish sings and they both make music together. Though poles apart in their lives, beliefs and backgrounds, Vaani and Krish are perfect with each other and for each other. Will they understand that truth despite their age, their problems? 

They say flawed, imperfect people make for a perfect love story…and Saiyaara is about celebrating that one love story that is so deep, so pure and so caring that it is absolutely unconditional.

Vaani and Krish will have to navigate life, their problems, their insecurities to hopefully realise that only love can be the answer to everything. Saiyaara is a film that celebrates every season of love through the eyes of Vaani & Krish and poses a simple question…do you love someone so much that you would bet everything to keep that person in your life?

Yuji Itadori is a boy with tremendous physical strength, though he lives a completely ordinary high school life. One day, to save a classmate who has been attacked by curses, he eats the finger of Ryomen Sukuna, taking the curse into his own soul. From then on, he shares one body with Ryomen Sukuna. Guided by the most powerful of sorcerers, Satoru Gojo, Itadori is admitted to Tokyo Jujutsu High School, an organization that fights the curses... and thus begins the heroic tale of a boy who became a curse to exorcise a curse, a life from which he could never turn back.

snippet.description:

Lyrics:

(Afusic) 

Mere is dil pe haavi hay
Tu is duniya se pyari hay
Jo bhoolun main to kuch sajna 
Kami peshi ki muafi hay 

Han jaltay hain kanwal tujh se 
Tu jag mera sajati hay

Ye man bharta hay kab mera
Teri har pal hi khuahish hay

O janam

Sitam ye ham pe, janam kya dhaya 
tunay Nazar mila k, dil ko churaya 

Tunay ham suna hay 
Wapis na aya
Tere jaal main janam
Jo bhi phasa tu

Bal khaeee hyeeeee, tham jae dunya meri jaman mujhay ese na sataya kar
Jo tu muskurae, hyeeee, pheeka lagta hay har 1 manzar jana thora rehem khaya kar
x2
(Hasan Raheem)
Meri aarzu ko 
Fiza jaga nahi day 
Meri aarzu to 
Khiza ye har gayi hai 

Kuch hamarey ye qissay thay sachay say 
Kuch tumaron nay jo rang bharey 
Apko hum samaj ayen achay say 
Log azal say sabhi tang karain 

Izhaar ye kay 
Sab tabiyat kay mutabiq nahi  
Thoray hain karwey 
Par jaana hum munafiq nahi
  Izhaar ye kay
 Is aziyat ki ijazat nahi 
Maana hai karwey 
Par jaana munafiq nahi 

(Afusic)

Tu bal khaaye haaye tham jaaye dunya meri janam muje aisay na sataya kar 
Jo tu muskuraye haye pheeka lagta hai har ik manzar jaana thora reham khaaya kar x2
(Hasan Raheem)
Thora rehem khaya kar x4

snippet.title: Anuv Jain - Arz Kiya Hai (Official Lyrical Video)
snippet.description:
For centuries, poets have given voice to the human heart, shaping the language of love. #ArzKiyaHai carries that legacy forward as an intimate tribute rooted in India’s poetic tradition, embracing the unguarded honesty of speaking your heart. At its helm is India’s most popular independent artist, Anuv Jain, pairing delicate guitar work with achingly tender vocals that distill this very emotion into melody. Joining him is Indian electronic duo Lost Stories working their magic on the production of the track as well as performing on the harmonium.

Listen to Arz Kiya Hai: https://UMGI.lnk.to/ArzKiyaHai_CSBS3

CREDITS

Written, Composed, and Performed By: Anuv Jain
Producer: Lost Stories
Additional Production and Additional Vocals: Sarthak Kalyani
Backing Vocals: Solomon Konwar Rengme, Anahita Singh
Acoustic Guitars, Electric Guitars, Charango, Bass Guitars: Keba Jeremiah

Harmonium: Lalit Sisodiya
Electric Guitar: Angad Bahra
Bass Guitar: Vivian D'Souza

Mixed by Rishab Joshi (Lost Stories), Mukul Jain, Mastered by Mukul Jain

#CokeStudioBharat #ArzKiyaHai #AnuvJain
